    {
      "id": "9adffdf1_23ff07ac",
      "file_path": "bpmn/mso-infrastructure-bpmn/src/test/java/org/onap/so/bpmn/infrastructure/pnf/delegate/AaiConnectionTestImpl.java",
      "patchset_number": 4,
      "line": 40,
      "message": "1. Broken encapsulation - The added UUID_V4 is never used in this class, but referenced from CreateAndActivatePnfResourceTest. It should be defined there.\nSuggestion: also consider improving the definition of the other two constants by moving into the classes they are used in.\n\n2. While there is nothing wrong with having the UUID hardcoded as a String, I'd avoid specifying the version - a String is too fragile and susceptible to change. Consider generating the UUID deterministically for testing purposes",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 2815,
        "name": "Michal Kabaj",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "michal.kabaj@nokia.com",
        "username": "kabayashi"
      },
      "updated": "2018-12-10 10:25:23.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "9adffdf1_83835303",
      "file_path": "bpmn/so-bpmn-infrastructure-common/src/main/java/org/onap/so/bpmn/infrastructure/pnf/delegate/GenerateUuidDelegate.java",
      "patchset_number": 4,
      "line": 31,
      "message": "Suggestions - maybe it would be a good idea to indicate that the generated UUID is for PNF. Consider a small rename - GeneratePnfUuidDelegate or GenerateUuidForPnfDelegate. A similar change in the bpmn would also be required.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 2815,
        "name": "Michal Kabaj",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "michal.kabaj@nokia.com",
        "username": "kabayashi"
      },
      "updated": "2018-12-10 10:25:23.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "9adffdf1_a3af7793",
      "file_path": "bpmn/so-bpmn-infrastructure-common/src/main/java/org/onap/so/bpmn/infrastructure/pnf/delegate/PnfCheckInputs.java",
      "patchset_number": 4,
      "line": 41,
      "message": "Is this really a good choice to limit the UUID format verification only to V4 ?\nHave you tried implementing a validation approach that is more generic? Have you analyzed if UUID.fromString() would suffice (by catching IllegalArgumentsException) ?",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 2815,
        "name": "Michal Kabaj",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "michal.kabaj@nokia.com",
        "username": "kabayashi"
      },
      "updated": "2018-12-10 10:25:23.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
