      "patchset_number": 4,
      "line": 84,
      "message": "Yes it is true that there is a conflict. The main problem is with the camunda-bpm-assert artifact. The latest version 2.0-alpha is based on an old assertJ version: 1.7 which has some API incompatibilities with assertj 2/3. It is possible to use newest version of assertJ, but only in modules that do not require the camunda-bpm-assert depdendency. I've done some cleanup in poms with the assertj artifacts as part of the change https://gerrit.onap.org/r/#/c/72645/.\nBasically the main assertj version is 3.11.1, but it is overridden in modules using the camunda-bpm-assert with 1.7.0. This module requires 1.7.0.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 2815,
        "name": "Michal Kabaj",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "michal.kabaj@nokia.com",
        "username": "kabayashi"
      },
      "updated": "2018-12-10 14:43:40.000000000",
